PN,34802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1782233278
OL,3,CNottingham man waits to hear from
OL,4,Cfriend in train crash
OL,6,F"Just hoping and praying everyone's
OL,7,Floved ones and families come home
OL,8,Ftonight and wishing them a speedy
OL,9,Frecovery if there's any injuries.
OL,11,F"I don't know at the moment, and I
OL,12,Fdon't want to say if she's injured or
OL,13,Fnot injured.
OL,15,F"Trains travel at anything from 80 to
OL,16,F120 miles per hour, and being an F1
OL,17,Ffan that's pretty quick.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1782233278
OL,3,CNottingham man waits to hear from
OL,4,Cfriend in train crash
OL,6,F"When you see the closing speeds of a
OL,7,Ftrain when they come next to each
OL,8,Fother, you hear the big bang when they
OL,9,Fcome straight past each other, and to
OL,10,Fhear two trains have collided, that's
OL,11,Fpretty scary."
OL,13,FBritish Transport Police said shortly
OL,14,Fbefore 6.45pm: "We're responding to
OL,15,Freports of a collision involving two
OL,16,Ftrains in the Bedford area."
OL,26,@vD@POUxD@\O]
